snippet.textDisplay: I asked the last episode & I Gottttttttttt I asked if you'd do a close up of the fish thank you Brodie your freakin amazing I've not been to the Red Sea for a few years & it's nearly a 5 hr flight from the 🇬🇧 but I was talking about it at different parts how the reef is as I'm disabled I need to get to the reef from the beach & what you done I've done only today not anything like your other vlogs. I have got on the reef with a bag of cooked meat & come out in the parrot fish bites up my arms but as a sixty yr old woman I was well buzzing 😊 I remember going to the Maldives and it was first time I'd seen a moray with its head out the coral, a white tipped reef that came & had another look but I went coming out that water. Then under the jetty were a couple of yellow fin tuna & some evil looking & small Baracuda wow wow I came out & sat on the edge of the sea crying my hubby thought I was hurt because he don't swim. I said if I die today I'm so lucky. So that's why your vlogs get me every time but tonight I cried & realised what I'm missing so off to the Red Sea may or June. Thank you Brodie Moss for making my wish come true. I love you, Stryda, Dad Bod Iyla & the crew ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

Then under the jetty were a couple of yellow fin tuna & some evil looking & small Baracuda wow wow I came out & sat on the edge of the sea crying my hubby thought I was hurt because he don't swim.
